column1: Source: USDA Branded Food Products Database Release July 2018 Software v.3.9.5 2018-08-15
Nutrient data for: FOUR CHEESE & SAUSAGE PIZZA WITH GARLIC BUTTER SAUCE (NO RED SAUCE), UPC: 750369041816
Food Group:  Branded Food Products Database

CRUST: FLOUR, (WHEAT, MALTED BARLEY), WATER, SOYBEAN OIL, YEAST, SALT, DEXTROSE, LEAVENING (SODIUM ALUMINUM PHOSPHATE, SODIUM BICARBONATE), CALCIUM PROPIONATE (PRESERVATIVE) AND SOY LECITHIN. CHEESE: LOW MOISTURE PART-SKIM MOZZARELLA CHEESE (PASTEURIZED PART-SKIM MILK, CHEESE CULTURE, SALT, ENZYMES), PROVOLONE CHEESE (PASTEURIZED MILK, CHEESE CULTURE, SALT, ENZYMES), YELLOW CHEDDAR CHEESE (PASTEURIZED PART-SKIM MILK, CHEESE CULTURE, SALT, ENZYMES, ANNATTO), ROMANO CHEESE (PASTEURIZED PART-SKIM MILK, CHEESE CULTURE, SALT, ENZYMES), POWDERED CELLULOSE ADDED TO PREVENT CAKING. SAUSAGE: PORK, SALT, SPICE, GARLIC POWDER. SAUCE: LIQUID AND HYDROGENATED SOYBEAN OIL, SALT, NATURAL AND ARTIFICIAL FLAVORS, SOY LECITHIN, TBHQ AND CITRIC ACID ADDED TO PROTECT FLAVOR, BETA CAROTENE (COLOR), DIMETHYLPOLYSILOXANE, AND ANTI-FOAMING AGENT ADDED.
